Gift to Kim Jong Il  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by a delegation of the Viet Nam�|DPRK Friendship Association on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was conveyed to an official concerned on Aug. 1 by Pham Tat Dong, chairman of the association and chairman of the Educational Panel of the State Council of Education who is leading the delegation.

Philippine President on Friendly and Cooperative Relations with DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- Philippine President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo met the DPRK delegation headed by Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun on a visit to the Philippines and had a talk with it on July 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president said that she was pleased to see the positive development of the situation on the Korean Peninsula, adding that she would positively support the development of the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries in the future, too.

Abe Group's Moves to Disturb Six-Party Talks under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- Japan is keen to bar the improvement of its relations with the DPRK and derail the six-party talks aimed at settling the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula under the pretext of the "abduction issue." This is based on the calculation of the ultra-nationalist forces of Japan represented by Abe that the issue of access to nukes by the DPRK now in the hostile relationship with Japan can be used as a good pretext for turning it into a military power and its nuclear weaponization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in its signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Abe group is busy with its mendicant diplomacy aimed at internationalizing the issue of abduction and putting international pressure upon the DPRK, insisting that it has not yet been solved. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Abe is known to have regarded the "abduction issue" as a bargaining chip for the maintenance of his power and the realization of his political ambition. Some days ago, he let loose the jargon that he would buckle down to the settlement of the "abduction issue" with an "iron will." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are making much ado about the issue, but it had already found a solution thanks to the sincere efforts of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the investigation into the issue and its handling came to an end thanks to the sincere efforts of the DPRK, the Japanese reactionaries invented new "victims of abduction" by putting in motion the "society for the investigation into the issues of specified persons reported missing." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hundreds of people are reported missing in Japan every year and, therefore, the above-said forces may keep concocting new information about "abduction" as long as they are making much fuss about the "abduction issue" while staying in power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lurking behind the Abe regime's escalated provocations to the DPRK over the "abduction issue" are a sinister and wicked calculation and purpose. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's "departure from the postwar regime" touted by Abe upon assuming premiership is intended to help Japan get rid of the status of a defeated country subject to military restrictions and establish a war system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is Abe's calculation that Japan must avail itself of the "wind caused by the DPRK's access to nukes" in order to lay a military foundation for the "assertive diplomacy" oft-repeated by him and to this end it is necessary to deter the six-party talks from making any progress and buy time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There will be only complications and difficulties in the way of the talks if Japan continues disturbing the talks, persistently insisting on the already-settled "abduction issue" irrelevant to the mission and purport of the talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan would be left all alone and meet only frustration if it keeps standing in the way of the talks, making much ado about the "abduction issue."

Day of Korean People's Victory in War Observed in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- A meeting and film shows were held in Pakistan, the Czech Republic and Poland from July 22 to 24 on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of the victory of the Korean people in the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Secretary General of the Karachi Branch of the Pakistan�|Korea Friendship Association Zabed Ansari in his speech at the meeting said that the DPRK has a powerful army which has grown strong to be a-match-for-a hundred army under the care of Kim Jong Il and the might of the unbreakable unity of the leader, the party and the masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Union of Polish People's Army Roman Orszewski noted that the army and people of the DPRK under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung dealt at the U.S. imperialists who boasted of being the "strongest" in the world the heaviest blow in history, adding that their victory in the Fatherland Liberation War marked an event to be specially recorded in the world history of wars. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is now winning one victory after another in the fierce confrontation with the U.S. because the President and the leader have long built the capacity of the DPRK for self-defence with the Songun idea and Songun leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vice Dean of the Political Faculty of University of Damascus Saber Ballul in his statement on July 24 on the occasion of the 54th anniversary of the victory of the Korean people in the Fatherland Liberation War said should the United States keep pursuing aggression, oblivious of the lesson taught by history, it will certainly suffer a heavy defeat before the Korean people in the 21st century, too.

National Presentation of Maritime Science and Technology Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- A national presentation of maritime science and technology was held here on July 30 under the sponsorship of the Central Committee of the Korean General Federation of Science and Technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were scientists and technicians of the Hydro-Meteorological Service, institutes under the State Academy of Sciences, Kim Il Sung University, Kim Chaek University of Technology and Pyongyang University of Construction and Building Materials Production and other maritime fields and related scientific and educational institutions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants heard at least 70 papers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers introduced successes and experience gained in developing maritime science and technology and actively tapping and using marine resources including the research into the characteristics of the long-term change in maritime meteorology and climate on the coasts of Korea, the study of the law governing the work to correctly find out placer in the waters of the continental shelf in the East Sea of Korea and research aimed at protecting maritime ecological environment.

Withdrawal of U.S. Forces Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification reportedly issued a statement on July 27 demanding the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea and the dissolution of the war "alliance" with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement recalled that the U.S. has shipped nuclear weapons into south Korea for the last 54 years, thus increasing the danger of a nuclear war and reduced this land to a huge base of aggression forces and a nuclear arsenal according to its strategy for world domination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It accused the U.S. of deliberately creating an atmosphere of inter-Korean confrontation, hamstringing the efforts to implement the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities are driving innocent people to death by stepping up the arms buildup and troop dispatch pursuant to the U.S. policy of war of aggression, the statement noted, stressing: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to drive the U.S. forces out of south Korea and scrap the war "alliance" with the U.S. in order to achieve genuine peace on the Korean Peninsula.

Chinese Military, Naval and Air Attache Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- Sun Yanfeng, military, naval and air attache of the Chinese embassy here, hosted a reception at the embassy on July 31 on the occasion of the 80th anniversary of the foundation of the Chinese People's Liberation Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Vice-Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, Pak Jae Gyong, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, other general officers and officers of the KPA, officials concerned and diplomatic envoys and military attaches of embassies of different countries here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Xing Haiming, Chinese charge d'affaires ad interim, and staff members of the embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

Lao Parliamentary Delegation Feted  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Supreme People's Assembly hosted a reception in honor of the delegation of the National Assembly of the Lao People's Democratic Republic on a visit to the DPRK at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on July 31. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were members of the delegation of the National Assembly of the Lao People's Democratic Republic led by Thongsing Thammavong, president of the National Assembly who is member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party, the Lao charge d' affaires a.i. here and staff members of the Lao embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Chairman of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly Choe Thae Bok, Kim Wan Su who is chairman of the Korea-Laos Friendship Parliamentary Group, Deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly Pak Jong Sun, Hong So Hon and Kim Kwang Chol and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok in his speech said that the Lao people have achieved big success in their efforts for the economic development and stability of the country and national prosperity under the leadership of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He emphasized that the DPRK would boost the friendly and cooperative relations with Laos, guided by the idea of the foreign policy of independence, peace and friendship, and strive hard to build a new independent, peaceful and prosperous world with the progressive people of Asia and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thongsing Thammavong in his speech noted that Laos is pleased to see the dignity and influence power of the DPRK rising day by day, adding that this gives strong encouragement and valuable experience to the Lao People's Democratic Republic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the belief that their current visit would mark a meaningful occasion in boosting the traditional friendly relations between the two parties, states and peoples which were provided by President Kim Il Sung and President Kaysone Phomvihane and are now developing under the deep care of Kim Jong Il and President Choummaly Saynasone.

Foreign Delegations and Delegates Visit Old Home in Mt. Paektu
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Samjiyon, July 31 (KCNA) -- Delegations and delegates of Juche idea study organizations from different countries and regions on a tour of revolutionary battle sites in the area of Mt. Paektu Tuesday visited the old home of Kim Jong Il in the secret camp of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They, first of all, laid a floral basket and bouquets before the mosaic portraying the three generals of Mt. Paektu erected in the secret camp and paid respects to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They saw historic relics in the old home. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They held an oath-taking meeting there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers including Matteo Carbonelli, secretary general of the European Society for the Study of the Juche Idea, said Kim Jong Il's birth in the secret camp was a great auspicious event which promised a bright future in the shaping of the destiny of the Korean nation and in the revolutionary cause of Juche. An independent and peaceful new world is sure to be built thanks to him, they stressed, and expressed their resolution to develop in depth the study and dissemination of the Juche idea and Songun idea, true to his Songun leadership, thus making a tangible contribution to the accomplishment of the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the letter they said Mt. Paektu shining with the history of the great men is throwing ever brighter rays together with the great Songun politics as a symbol of world peace and justice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They further said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mt. Paektu is always the native place in the hearts not only of the Korean people but also of us fighting for a peaceful and independent new world under the banner of the Juche idea and of the progressives worldwide aspiring after independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Remaining true to our vow in Mt. Paektu, we will deepen the study and dissemination of the Juche idea on a higher stage, conscious of our pride and sense of duty as the pioneer of the Juche idea, and thereby make a sizable contribution to the independent development of countries and nations and the cause of global independence.

Independent Reunification Called for in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- South Korean national movement organizations including the "Federation of Homogeneous Nation Movement Organizations" and the "Tong-Hak Society for National Unification" reportedly held a meeting on the history of national independence in Seoul on July 28. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting said the Korean nation should not forget that the United States and Japan cooked up the criminal "Taft-Katsura Agreement" on July 29, 1905, 102 years ago, through which they worked hand in glove with each other to force the Koreans to experience the tragedy of losing the state power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all the Koreans in the north and the south and abroad to implement the June 15 joint declaration in close unity and achieve independent reunification without fail under the banner of "By our nation itself," not yielding to the pressure and blackmail of any outside forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration read out at the meeting proclaimed the period from July 29 to November 17, the day marking the lapse of 102 years since the "Ulsa Five-Point Treaty" was fabricated by the Japanese imperialists, as a period of the national independent history movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called for waging a strenuous movement to decisively frustrate the crafty reinvasion moves of Japan which is covetous of the Korean Peninsula again, remove the danger of the outbreak of another war gathering over the Korean Peninsula and achieve peaceful reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration appealed to all the fellow countrymen to firmly adhere to the main spirit of the June 15 joint declaration and wage a strenuous struggle to surely achieve the peaceful reunification of the country by pooling efforts and wisdom of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged the United States and Japan to deeply reflect on and apologize for the crimes they had committed against the Korean nation.

Sound-Recognition Program Ryongnamsan Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- To develop a sound-recognition program is a cutting edge scientific and technical index in the IT Era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Young scientists in their twenties at Computer Science College under Kim Il Sung University of the DPRK, have developed the Korean sound-recognition program Ryongnamsan, which is of great practical significance in the development of information science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The program can input the text according to sound, edit the document and search files. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A section chief of the Operating System Research and Development Centre Kim Tok Ho told KCNA: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The program can recognize more than 96% of what any people say in Korean and its real-time recognition speed is five letters per second. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Along with the edition of document, it can operate computer and turn telephone dial by name and thus makes it possible to save much manpower, time and funds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The program is being applied to different sectors in Korea.

Mt. Paektu, Ancestral Mountain of Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- Mt. Paektu, a famous mountain of Korea, has been called as an ancestral mountain from olden times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mountain, which had been called as Pulham, Tothae, Thaebaek and Paek Mountains, was fixed as Mt. Paektu in the middle of the seventh century. In the light of its geological and geographical view, the mountain constitutes the origin of all the mountains and ranges of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 1,470-kilometer long Grand Paektu Range runs from Mt. Paektu to Kujae Peak (Hadong County, South Kyongsang Province) in the coast of the South Sea at the end of Jiri Range, via Mts. Turyu and Thaebaek. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Su Gwang, a pioneer of realism in Korea, wrote in his book "Jibongryusol" that the Paektu Range stretches southward through Chol Pass on Machonryong Range to form Mts. Kumgang, Odae and Thaebaek and ends at Mt. Jiri. He stressed that Paektu Range continues to extend under the sea to link all the islands of Japan and that Mt. Hanna is also part of the range. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mt. Paektu is a famous and ancestral mountain of Korea. It is well illustrated by a map, appendix to the book "Sinjungdonggukyojisungram" published in the 16th century, the "Taedongyo Map" made by Kim Jong Ho in 1861 and other maps. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation has regarded Mt. Paektu as the birthplace of the national state and holy mountain associated with soul of the nation. According to historical records including "Samguksagi", "Kusamguksa" and "Samgukyusa", such orthodox states in Korea as Koguryo, Palhae and Koryo from Kojoson (ancient Korea), the first state, asserted that the state foundation was directly connected with Mt. Paektu and the states were built in the spirit of the mountain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean ancestors worshiped the mountain generation to generation. It observed a custom to perform a sacrificial rite for the God of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koryo people related Koguryo with Mt. Paektu and believed the God of the mountain as guardian of Koryo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the period of Ri Dynasty, people began to connect Tangun, founder of Korea, with the mountain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tangun tale, which is told in Miyama, Kagosima Prefecture, Japan also tells that Tangun is connected with Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today, Mt. Paektu is widely known as not only the famous and ancestral mountain of Korea but also the sacred place and mountain of the revolution.

Talks Held between SPA of DPRK and Lao National Assembly
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- Talks between Choe Thae Bok, chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, and Thongsing Thammavong, president of the National Assembly of Laos, were held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on the issue of boosting the friendly and cooperative relations between the two assemblies and matters of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the DPRK side were Kim Wan Su, chairman of the DPRK-Laos Friendship Parliamentary Group, and others and from the Lao side members of the delegation of the National Assembly of Laos and the Lao charge d' affaires ad interim to the DPRK.

Remains of More Martyrs Buried in Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- Remains of more martyrs were buried in the Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They included Kwak Chil Song, former officer of the Korean People's Army who took an active part in the anti-Japanese struggle before the liberation of the country and made a contribution to the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War by ferreting out the enemy's operational plan, Han Ju Gyong, former KPA general officer who devoted himself to the reunification of the country while working at the then Military Armistice Commission, and Thae Son Hui, former KPA general officer who was well known as the first woman pilot of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also among them were Most Venerable Pak Thae Hwa, former chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Buddhist Federation, Jon Hyong Gyu, former announcer of the Korean Radio and TV Broadcasting Committee, Im Sa Jun, former creator of the ceramic work creative group of the Mansudae Art Studio, and Jon Ho Son, former adviser of the Kumgang Guidance Bureau who made a contribution to the exploration of underground resources of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Burial ceremonies took place on August 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Song Yong Su, deputy director of the History Institute of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and officials concerned and bereaved families. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the ceremonies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The remains of the martyrs were buried in the graves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants laid wreaths and bouquets before the graves of the martyrs and paid silent tribute to them.

Extravaganza "Arirang" Staged Again 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- The grand gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang", a "Kim Il Sung Prize" laureate, was staged again at the May Day Stadium Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stadium was packed to its capacity with tens of thousands of people from all walks of life. It was gorgeously decorated with floats depicting Mt. Paektu, a variety of illuminations and multi-colored electronic displays, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the lilting melody of song "Pyongyang Is Best" resounded forth, "Highest tribute to the great leader, the father of the nation", "Greatest glory to the great leader Comrade Kim Jong Il" and other huge letters appeared on the background one after another and the floor of the stadium turned into a sea of flower-waving and dancing performers before the performance began. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance re-represented on the occasion of the Day of the Sun made a grand epic depiction of the magnificent appearance of Korea of Juche making all-out advance towards the high eminence of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation while demonstrating its might as a dignified sovereign power after putting an end to the history of the nation full of ordeals as it held the most outstanding leader in high esteem as its father, and the Korean people's desire and will to accomplish the cause of national reunification by the concerted efforts of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The extravaganza led the audience to a mysterious and fascinating world of art as it was a good combination of dynamic mass gymnastic displays, the presentation of beautiful and elegant arts and vast veritable moving background. The performance was highly acclaimed by them at the turn of each scene.

Kim Jong Il Inspects Command of KPA Combined Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected the command of KPA Combined Unit 264. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He dropped in at the operation commanding room to learn about the unit's performance of duty from its commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth the tasks to be fulfilled by the unit to increase its combat capability in every way, expressing satisfaction over the fact that its servicepersons have consolidated the military fortress of Korean-style socialism as firm as an invulnerable iron wall by thoroughly implementing the WPK's military line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he looked round the gymnasium, vegetable greenhouse and other places of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greatly pleased to learn that the unit has successfully built supply service facilities to improve the servicepersons' living and facilities for strengthening their physical training and made an effective use of them and that it is supplying fresh vegetables to them in all seasons by constructing vegetable greenhouses of high economic value, in particular. He appreciated the efforts exerted by the commanding officers of the unit for providing its servicepersons with good living conditions by paying deep attention to the supply service. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round the compound of the unit kept neat and tidy like a park, he said that this vividly shows the proud appearance of the KPA which has inherited the lifestyle of the Anti-Japanese Guerilla Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that in recent years the unit has done a lot of things in all aspects including the work to bolster its combat capability and its management, he highly appreciated its achievements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of his inspection he together with servicepersons of the combined unit enjoyed an art performance given by its art squad at the servicepersons' hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Greatly pleased to see the splendid performance high in ideological value and artistry given by the squad, he highly praised it for its successful performance and militant art activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Hwang Pyong So and Kim Sung Yon, vice department directors of the WPK Central Committee.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona una subunidad de Unidad No 4318 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 1 de agosto (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, inspecciono una subunidad adscrita a la Unidad No. 4318 del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El Comandante Supremo hizo conocimiento del estado de cumplimiento del deber por ella y recorrio el interior y el exterior del cuartel recien construido. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En su recorrido por el cuartel elegante y comodo y otras instalaciones de varios tipos, se mostro muy satisfecho de la magnifica construccion del primer edificio moderno y expreso su agradecimiento a los militares participantes en la obra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Destaco que los uniformados de aqui terminaron esta obra con sus propias fuerzas buscando y empleando activamente los materiales locales y elogio que esto resulta un brillante producto del espiritu de apoyarse en las propias fuerzas y del noble patriotismo del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Seguidamente, recorrio la sala de educacion, dormitorio, comedor, bano, deposito de alimentos subsidiarios, lugar de descanso al aire libre, corral, invernadero y otros puntos del destacamento prestando mucha atencion al trabajo y la vida de los militares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Alabo a los comandantes y los soldados de la subunidad por haber acondicionado excelentemente, uniendo sus voluntades, el interior y el exterior del cuartel y las instalaciones culturales, educacionales y de intendencia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En la epoca del Songun (priorizacion militar), nuestro ejercito produjo un cambio radical en todos los aspectos como el rasgo ideoespiritual, el moral, el entrenamiento politico-combativo, la regularizacion y la administracion de la unidad cumpliendo satisfactoriamente el papel de vanguardia en calidad del grueso de la revolucion, asevero el Comandante Supremo y anadio que estas preciosas hazanas atesoradas por el heroico EPC son la firme garantia de la victoria de la revolucion del Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Acto seguido, el Comandante Supremo se fotografio junto a los militares de la subunidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Le acompanaron los subjefes de departamento del CC del PTC, Hwang Pyong So y Kim Sung Yon.

Rodong Sinmun reitera su critica a la banda de Abe
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 1 de agosto (ATCC) -- Al tratar de impedir el saneamiento de las relaciones Corea-Japon cuestionando el problema de secuestro, las fuerzas ultranacionalistas del pais isleno pretenden llevar al fracaso las conversaciones a 6 bandas y entorpecer la solucion del problema nuclear de la Peninsula Coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ademas, esta horda representada por Abe piensa que puede tomar por la justificacion de la conversion en una potencia militar y del armamentismo nuclear de Japon la posesion de armas nucleares por la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea que se halla en relaciones hostiles con este pais isleno. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Adelanta asi el diario Rodong Sinmun en un comentario individual difundido este miercoles y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al insistir en la irresolucion del problema de secuestro, la banda de Abe lanza una intensa campana diplomatica mendicante a fin de internacionalizarlo e imponer una presion internacional a la RPDC por el respecto. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Abe, quien considera ese tema como la carta principal para mantenerse en el poder y alcanzar su ambicion politica, se decidio recientemente a trabajar para su solucion con una "voluntad ferrea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Pero, ese asunto escandalizado por los reaccionarios islenos ya fue resuelto gracias a los esfuerzos sinceros de la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Una vez terminadas la investigacion y la gestion del problema gracias a las medidas magnanimas de la RPDC, esos elementos japoneses inventaron nuevas "victimas de secuestro" por conducto de la llamada "Sociedad de investigacion del problema de los desaparecidos especificos".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Es del todo posible que se inventen uno tras otro en Japon nuevos "datos de secuestrados" ya que en este pais se reportan al ano centenares de desaparecidos y se lanza una acalorada campana en cuanto al "rapto" de las fuerzas ultranacionalistas encabezadas por Abe en el poder. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el trasfondo de la escalada de estas maniobras provocativas a la RPDC se halla un siniestro y malsano objetivo del ejecutivo de Abe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al tomar la posesion de premier, Abe abogo por la "salida de Japon del sistema posbelico" en su intento de sacarlo de la situacion del pais derrotado en la guerra, que se ve restringido en el campo militar, e implantar luego un sistema belico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para sentar el cimiento militar de la "diplomacia de criterio propio", de la cual Abe no se cansa de hablar, hay que aprovechar el "viento de posesion de armas nucleares del Norte de Corea" y ganar el tiempo al frenar la marcha de las conversaciones a 6 bandas pretextando el problema de secuestro. He aqui la astuta intencion de aquellos reaccionarios japoneses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Si Japon sigue cuestionando obstinadamente ese polemico asunto, ya liquidado y desvinculado totalmente a la mision y el proposito de la cita a 6 bandas, solo creara complicaciones y escollos en ella y quedara aislado y perjudicado.

Mas de 150 casos de espionaje aereo contra la RPDC en julio
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 1 de agosto (ATCC) -- Segun una fuente castrense, en el mes recien expirado, se registraron mas de 150 casos de espionaje aereo contra la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea por parte de los aviones estrategicos y tacticos de diferentes misiones de los imperialistas norteamericanos y del ejercito surcoreano. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El 30 de julio, un "U-2" realizo durante muchas horas la ida y vuelta del Este al Oeste dedicandose al reconocimiento electronico y la filmacion sobre toda la extension de la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Entre los dias 24 y el 26, un "E-3", procedente de una base en ultramar, hizo otro tanto sobre los objetivos en las profundidades de la parte Norte, al tiempo que comandaba en el espacio aereo del Sur de Corea las escuadrillas enfrascadas en los ejercicios de apoyo aereo a corta distancia y de asistencia a las tropas terrestres. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Los dias 5 y 18, un "EP-3" sobrevolo las zonas litorales de los Mares Oeste y Este de Corea rastreando los blancos importantes de la parte Norte en la primera linea del frente y los objetivos submarinos en ambos mares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
